node.title: Verdict reached in federal hate crimes trial for killing of Ahmaud Arbery
node.description: Travis McMichael, Gregory McMichael and William "Roddie" Bryan were convicted of murder and other charges in November.

node.title: Oil prices near $100 a barrel as Ukraine crisis deepens
node.description: Mounting concerns over the conflict are hitting global financial markets driving up crude prices to an eight-year high.

node.title: Britney Spears reportedly signs $15 million book deal
node.description: Britney's sister, Jamie Lynn Spears, recently released a book of her own that led to a very public feud.

node.title: Soccer stars Rapinoe and Morgan on $24M settlement: "Equal pay from here on out"
node.description: The settlement includes backpay for previous World Cup prize money.

node.title: Troops on Ukraine's front line struggle to predict Putin's next move
node.description: A war that simmered for 8 years in eastern Ukraine has ramped up, and troops in the trenches tell CBS News they don't know what to expect next from Russia's leader.

node.title: "That is not my son!": Texas father discovers wrong body in coffin
node.description: Two bodies were incorrectly identified at several points, leading to their being switched and even the wrong one being cremated, CBS Dallas reports.

node.title: Explosion at gold mining site kills dozens: "Bodies everywhere"
node.description: The explosion was believed to have been caused by chemicals used to treat gold that were stocked at the site.

node.title: U.S. imposes sanctions after Putin recognizes breakaway Ukraine regions
node.description: White House press secretary Jen Psaki said the penalties are "separate from and would be in addition to the swift and severe economic measures" the U.S. has been preparing with allies.

node.title: Homemade rocket fuel displaces 22 students at BYU dorm
node.description: The failed DIY-experiment was a "volatile mixture" that engulfed the walls in flames, police said.

node.title: Jane "Nightbirde" Marczewski, "AGT" contestant, dies at 31
node.description: She was suffering from cancer. She'd stunned the "America's Got Talent" judges with her performance of an original song called "It's OK."

node.title: Biden has started interviewing Supreme Court candidates
node.description: The president previously said he has narrowed his list down to four choices. He is expected to announce a nominee by the end of February.

node.title: Colombia partially decriminalizes abortion
node.description: Abortion advocates say the country's ruling is a "triumph for human rights."

node.title: U.S. and allies vow new sanctions over Putin's "act of war" in Ukraine
node.description: Ukraine's defense chief says Russian leader has taken "another step towards the revival of the Soviet Union," as Germany halts "Nord Stream 2" gas pipeline.

node.title: 16-year-old chess prodigy stuns world champion Magnus Carlsen
node.description: Rameshbabu Praggnanandhaa is the youngest to beat Carlsen since the Norwegian became world champion in 2013.

node.title: Illinois man held on $1 million bail for alleged anti-gay attack
node.description: Authorities said Ethan Dickerson allegedly threatened to kill the victim in a homophobic rant.

node.title: "Family Reunion" actress Jaida Benjamin missing
node.description: The 27-year-old was last seen Saturday in Studio City, L.A. police say.

node.title: Tonga gets internet service back five weeks after volcanic eruption
node.description: It mangled a large swath of the undersea cable linking the Pacific nation to the rest of the world.

node.title: "AGT" contestant Jane "Nightbirde" Marczewski dies at 31
node.description: She was suffering from cancer. She'd stunned the "America's Got Talent" judges with her performance of an original song called "It's OK."

node.title: Heartland Group posts $47m half-year profit
node.description: Financial services company Heartland Group's bottom line has grown on the back of increased lending and higher margins.

node.title: Incoming travellers to get pack with 3 rapid antigen tests - Ardern
node.description: Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern says travellers coming into Auckland Airport will be issued with a pack including three rapid antigen tests, information and advice.

node.title: 'A mockery of the justice system': Rapist plays rugby in Fiji while serving sentence
node.description: Fiji's Ministry for Women and a human rights advocate have condemned Amenoni Nasilasila participation in the Wardens rugby sevens side.

node.title: Final "Arthur" episode airs after 25 seasons
node.description: The show was first broadcast in 1996, and fans of all ages tuned in to the last episode and shared their thoughts on social media.

node.title: Covid-19: cases growing in Whanganui
node.description: Covid-19 is continuing its spread into central and western parts of the North Island, with active cases now confirmed in Rangitīkei, Whanganui and the Ruapehu district.

node.title: Heaphy Bridge on Great Walk irreparable
node.description: The flood-damaged Heaphy Bridge on the Heaphy Track has been written off by structural engineers and cannot be fixed.

node.title: Covid-19 update: 2846 community cases, 143 in hospital
node.description: There are 2846 Covid-19 cases in the community today and 143 people in hospital with the virus, the Ministry of Health reports.

node.title: Field hospital plan for Northland unlikely to come to fruition, DHB says
node.description: The Northland DHB says a field hospital in its pandemic plan is "extremely unlikely" to be used.

node.title: NZ Paralympians 'ready to get into it'
node.description: The New Zealand Paralympic team heads to Beijing this week, excited about competition after watching the Olympic Games.

node.title: Political leaders should 'get off their high horses' - Jim Bolger
node.description: Former prime minister Jim Bolger says political leaders should "get off their high horses" and meet with those occupying Parliament's lawn.

node.title: Emergency ambulance won't enter protest zone after hostility
node.description: Wellington's only emergency ambulance service will no longer attend emergencies within the protest area at Parliament.

node.title: Govt make $200k funding available as ex-Cyclone Dovi re-classified
node.description: The government has classified ex-cyclone Dovi as a medium-scale adverse event, making $200,000 of funding available to help recovering efforts.
